  "course_description": "History of the relationship between the American people, land, weather, and natural resources, with special attention to the environmental movement since 1960.",
  "course_notes": "(Same as ENVS 344 1) The history of the relationship between people, plants, animals, climate, and the landscape throughout American history. Topics include agriculture, whaling, gold and oil rushes, forestry, conservation, Native American adaptation to the environment, extinction, the history of ecology, the rise of environmentalism as a political and social movement in the Twentieth Century, and growing concerns over climate change. Two midterms, two short papers, and a final exam.",
